  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This pilot trail aims to assess the effectiveness of ECA cream in the treatment of calcifying
      shoulder tendinitis in terms of:

        1. Reduction or removal of shoulder calcifications

        2. Functional improvements

        3. Pain improvements 10 subjects will be assessed prior and 1 and 2 months post
           intervention onset. The intervention will consist in the application of the ECA cream in
           the affected shoulder twice a day during 1 month.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
